==English==
{{Wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From Latin meaning "love, sexual desire, loveliness, beauty, charm", possibly from the Sanskrit ''vanas'', (desire).

===Proper noun===
'''Venus'''

# (''Roman mythology''): the [[goddess]] of [[love]], [[beauty]], and [[natural]] [[productivity]]
# the second [[planet]] in our [[solar system]]

====Derived terms====
*[[venereal]]
*[[venusian]]<!-- capitalisation? -->

